---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>üßë‚ÄçüöÄ Hello, Inventor.</h1>
			<p>
				Embedded systems have gained popularity amongst the masses over the years. In the recent past, this has been accelerated by availability of prototyping boards at all levels, from Arduino to Launchpads to Raspberry Pi and beyond. 
				<a href="https://astro.build/">Astro</a> 
			</p>
			<p>
				Arduino has been a good example of adoption due to ease of entry and has done the job well. Now, time has come to move on.....move from entry level to advanced programming, move from LED Blinkies to LiFi applications, move from ultrasonic range finding to Time of Flight sensing (of Light !!), move from power guzzlers to Ultra Low power (Power and Forget !!).
				<a href="https://astro.build/">Astro</a> 
			</p>
			<p>
				<b>Let us move on with Mispino....</b>an Arduino compatible (Energia based) eco-system developed to bring in new concepts, evolve new use cases and exploit modern sensors & actuators. Let us get down to Rapid Application Development from Rapid Concept Demonstration.
				<code>astro.config.mjs</code>
				<a href="https://astro.build/integrations">Astro Integrations</a>
			</p>
			<p>Here are a few ideas on how to get started with the template:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Edit this page in <code>src/pages/index.astro</code></li>
				<li>Edit the site header items in <code>src/components/Header.astro</code></li>
				<li>Add your name to the footer in <code>src/components/Footer.astro</code></li>
				<li>Check out the included blog posts in <code>src/content/blog/</code></li>
				<li>Customize the blog post page layout in <code>src/layouts/BlogPost.astro</code></li>
			</ul>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
